<li id="cite_note-etymology-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-etymology_22-0" title="">^</a></b> Ukrainian <i>holod</i> (голод, ‘hunger’, compare Russian <i>golod</i>) should not be confused with <i>kholod</i> (холод, ‘cold’). For details, see <a href="/wiki/Romanization_of_Ukrainian" title="Romanization of Ukrainian">romanization of Ukrainian</a>. <i>Mor</i> means ‘plague’ in the sense of a disastrous evil or affliction, or a sudden unwelcome outbreak. See <a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/plague" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:plague">wiktionary:plague</a>.</li>
